content.description: Undercling start (with choss) bump crimp up to the flake, and top out.
content.location: The first boulder encountered at Camp Group site A.  See photo.

content.description: SDS low and right in The Pit and moves up the face to mantle topout.
content.protection: Pad on the higher rock that you would probably hit if you peeled.  Otherwise you'll fall right into the pit.
content.location:
In the center of the Group A boulder cluster, faces north.  See photos. 

Overhanging Boulder uphill and more or less in the center of the Group A boulder cluster.  The overhanging face faces north.  Problems start in a pit.  Worth a session if you have done everything else.

content.description: Starts in a pit on two good holds, traverses upwards then to the left to a good jug.  The slap up the top and mantle out.
Start on two slopey holds in a seam with a slopey heel hook.  Then slap your way up the pointed arete and finish the problem.
content.location: See photo.  Less than 5 feet away from Dungeons.

content.description: Start low and left in the pit at an obvious jug at eye level.  Move up and round the corner to your right onto the face and up arete to mantle topout.  Hard to avoid the butt-dab on the rock behind you.
content.protection: Pad on the ledge behind you.  You will fall into the pit if you peel.
content.location:
In the center of the Group A boulder cluster, the face faces north. 

Overhanging Boulder uphill and more or less in the center of the Group A boulder cluster.  The overhanging face faces north.  Problems start in a pit.  Worth a session if you have done everything else.

content.description:
This line starts low and left, same as Cool Hand Luke.  Come around the corner with heel hooks and keep going up the thin rail to topout on center of face.   

Overhanging Boulder uphill and more or less in the center of the Group A boulder cluster.  The overhanging face faces north.  Problems start in a pit.  Worth a session if you have done everything else.
content.protection: Pad.  Don't fall into the pit.
content.location: In the center of the Group A boulder cluster, the face faces north.

content.description: Many slabs of sandstone/quartzite conglomerate, that lend themselves to being a unique style at the Dodge.
